  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Typical elements include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Withdrawing the \"cleaned\" money and using it as seemingly legitimate income\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve intentionally disguising the origins of criminally derived funds.",
